						<summary>

						<p>Nandi-pillar under a pipal tree in the village.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Achyutadēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1460, (expired), Viḷambi, Pushya ba. 30, Sunday, Ardhōdaya,</hi> corresponding to 1539 A.D., January 19.</p>						

						<p>Slightly damaged. It records that the village Gōṅkavaram situated in the Mosalimaḍugusīma was restored as a <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> gift to the original donees of the village <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> Timmappanāyuḍu, son of Mallappa-Nāyuḍu and another by the king.</p>						

						</summary>
